{
  "stem": "12768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And so it was, it was hard time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And in Denmark, it gets awfully cold in the wintertime.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I think in 1942 and 1943 was the hardest winters that we ever had until actually this year, where it beats all records, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It, it got so cold that you could actually walk on the ice between Denmark and Sweden.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And that's about eight miles across.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So of course, so our people shouldn't escape from Denmark, the Germans sent their ice breakers out all the time, you know, to clear the strait.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And-- excuse me-- that was actually where we were going to school, enjoying-- we had a summer home outside Copenhagen what was in a place called Hornbaek.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "It was such a beautiful ride up to the summer house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was called the, the French Riviera in, in, in Denmark, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "You had to drive up along the coastline.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And it's all water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And it's, it's really beautiful to, to see.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And so we had a fairly good time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And when it was a big Jewish holidays, we always went to, to synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And we had family, friends, like the Ginsberg, the [NON-ENGLISH], and whatever else people or some friends.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And those were people I knew because my parents played bridge with the elder group.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "But on  big holidays, we always got together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And of course, around holiday time, we-- my mother had [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] two, three sisters.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "The one we didn't see so often.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "She lived far away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "But the other two lived right around us in, in Hellerup and Charlottenlund.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "So on one holiday, we were at our house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And on the next holiday, or the second holiday, we were at my one aunt's house, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
